         <div type="translation">
            <ab>MH 2718, recto: (1) Paoubestis, son of Psenamounis, has paid together with ----- to the bank [for silver of poll] (2) of year 43, 5 staters and surcharge of 1/2 kite, 1 1/2 obols. Written in year 43 of [Caesar], (3) Choiach 22. Signed Kephalos, son of Epikrates.</ab>
